-the-two-ways-that-western-civilisation-could-collapse":{"urn":"urn:pubstack:jative:article:future\u002Farticle\u002F20170818-the-two-ways-that-western-civilisation-could-collapse","_id":"5e982098272a584021aafa5d","ambientVideo":"","articleType":"video","assetVideo":[],"author":[],"bodyIntro":"Downfalls of great societies have often been preceded by a specific chain of events – could history be repeating itself? The one-minute video above explains what those triggers are.","businessUnit":"worldwide","cards":[{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EFor an in-depth read about how today&rsquo;s societies could fall apart, read more here:\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cul\u003E \u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20170418-how-western-civilisation-could-collapse\"\u003EHow Western civilisation could collapse\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fli\u003E \u003C\u002Ful\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHere&rsquo;s an extract:\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003E&ldquo;\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003ECollapses have occurred many times in human history, and no civilisation, no matter how seemingly great, is immune to the vulnerabilities that may lead a society to its end. Regardless of how well things are going in the present moment, the situation can always change. Putting aside species-ending events like an asteroid strike, nuclear winter or deadly pandemic, history tells us that it&rsquo;s usually a plethora of factors that contribute to collapse. What are they, and which, if any, have already begun to surface? It should come as no surprise that humanity is currently on an unsustainable and uncertain path &ndash; but just how close are we to reaching the point of no return?&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E-\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003EAPOCALYPSE WEEK\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fstrong\u00